body:
I need access to the bytes of an SKBitmap.
The code below always returns width \* height \* 4 as the value of pixelsPtr:

```
using (SKBitmap bmp = new SKBitmap(width, height, SKColorType.Bgra8888, SKAlphaType.Premul))
{
    IntPtr pixelsPtr = IntPtr.Zero;
    bmp.LockPixels();
    bmp.GetPixels(out pixelsPtr);
    bmp.UnlockPixels();
}

```
